SIMPLE: excellence
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Excellence
<hw>Ex"cel*lence</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>excellence</ets>, L. <ets>excellentia</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The quality of being excellent; state of possessing good qualities
in an eminent degree; exalted merit; superiority in virtue.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Consider first that great⟦br⟧
Or bright infers not <qex>excellence</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An excellent or valuable quality; that by which any
one excels or is eminent; a virtue.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With every <qex>excellence</qex> refined.</q>
<rj><qau>Beattie.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A title of honor or respect; -- more common in the
form <altname>excellency</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I do greet your <qex>excellence</qex>⟦br⟧
With letters of commission from the king.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Superiority; pre⟦eum⟧minence; perfection; worth;
goodness; purity; greatness.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Excellency</ent>⟦br⟧
